What is a Filesystem?
It is a system used by an operating system to manage files.
The system controls how data is saved or retrieved.
eg: ext3,ext4,xfs - linux filesystems
    NTFS,FAT - windows filesystems

File system structure and its description
/boot - contains file that is used by the boot loader(grub.cfg)
/root - root user home directory. It is not same as /
/dev  - system devices (e.g disk,cdrom,speakers,fashdrive,keyboard etc.)
/etc  - Configuration files applications runs on top of linux system 
        all those config files located here.
        make a backup before you modify any file.
/bin -> /usr/bin - Everyday user commands
/sbin -> /usr/sbin - System/filesystem commands
/opt -> Optional add-on applications (Not part of OS apps) 
        third party applications(oracle,mysql etc..)
/proc -> Running processes (Only exist in Memory)
/lib -> usr/lib - C programming library files needed by commands and apps
                  commands that we run like(pwd,ls,cat etc..)
                  strace -e open pwd
/tmp - Directory for temporary files.
/home - Directory for user
/var  = System logs (os writes some o/p app logs goes into this 
troubleshooting can we seen here
/run  - system daemons that start very early(eg: systemd and udev) to stroe temporary runtime files like PID files
/mnt - To mount external filesystem (eg.NFS)
/media - For cdrom mounts.

check in linux system.

Navigating File System:
-----------------------
important commands.
cd - change directory
pwd - print working directory
ls - list the directories & files.

Linux File or Directory Properties:
-----------------------------------
each file or directory in linux has detail information or properties.
ls -l 
Type       of links  Owner  Group Size  Month Day Time Name

drwxr-xr-x  21        root   root  4096  mar  11  14:03 var

lrwxrwxrwx  1         root   root  7   mar     11  14:04 testfile.txt

second column: 2nd hard links of file. subdirectories
third : who owns this file
4th : which group owns it
5th : size of file/directory
6th : day
7th : time
8th : name of file/directory














 










